SKYRIM SOMATIC COMPONENT SYSTEM
Spell Modification Through Understanding Magical Structure

CORE CONCEPT
Every spell in Skyrim is built from somatic components—fundamental relationships to magical law that express how a mage channels and shapes Magicka. By understanding these components, a mage can swap one component for another, creating a new variant of the spell without changing its base cost or damage.
This is not spell invention. This is spell mastery.

THE TWELVE SOMATIC COMPONENTS
1. PETITION
Definition: Request the law to work as it naturally inclines
 Essence: Working with natural forces, not against them
 Schools: Restoration, Illusion
 Effect on Spells: Easier to control, less chaotic, more subtle, works through gentle persuasion
2. COMMAND
Definition: Force the law to work as you will it
 Essence: Overpowering natural forces through sheer will
 Schools: Destruction, Conjuration
 Effect on Spells: Harder to manage, more dramatic, more violent, works through dominance
3. ANCHOR
Definition: Ground yourself in unshakeable conviction
 Essence: Your will becomes fixed and resistant to disruption
 Schools: Alteration, Restoration
 Effect on Spells: Resists interruption, persists longer, tied to caster's body, harder to dispel
4. PROJECT
Definition: Extend your will across distance
 Essence: Your effect travels and spreads
 Schools: Destruction, Conjuration, Illusion
 Effect on Spells: Reaches further, affects larger areas, disperses over distance
5. SHIFT
Definition: Allow the law to bend and flow
 Essence: Effect changes form or adapts to circumstances
 Schools: Alteration, Illusion
 Effect on Spells: Can chain through obstacles, adapts to terrain, effects are fluid and unpredictable
6. BIND
Definition: Fix a moment so it cannot unravel
 Essence: Lock changes in place permanently
 Schools: Conjuration, Alteration, Restoration
 Effect on Spells: Duration extends, effects persist strongly, hard to undo, targets become rooted
7. RELEASE
Definition: Surrender control and let the law reassert itself
 Essence: Effect is temporary and naturally unstable
 Schools: Destruction, Illusion
 Effect on Spells: Costs less to maintain, dissipates quickly, easily broken, naturally disperses
8. STABILIZE
Definition: Entropy is slow; this state is permanent
 Essence: Resist all change back to Base-State
 Schools: Alteration, Restoration
 Effect on Spells: Dramatically extended duration, immune to dispelling, caster must concentrate
9. ATTUNE
Definition: Become one with the law's expression
 Essence: You are not separate from this magic; you are its voice
 Schools: All equally
 Effect on Spells: Gain insight into deeper effects, secondary phenomena manifest, spell becomes partially automatic
10. SEVER
Definition: Break connections and shatter bonds
 Essence: Cut through links and bindings
 Schools: Destruction, Conjuration
 Effect on Spells: Disrupts other magic, breaks hostile effects, sunders conjured things
11. CONCEAL
Definition: Happen where no one is looking
 Essence: Work in silence and shadow
 Schools: Illusion, Conjuration
 Effect on Spells: Subtle and hard to notice, enemies have disadvantage detecting it, works unseen
12. REVEAL
Definition: All hidden things are shown
 Essence: Make the invisible visible and obvious
 Schools: Restoration, Illusion
 Effect on Spells: Dramatically obvious, highlights what's hidden, draws attention, hard to miss

BASELINE SPELL STRUCTURES
Spells are structured by their tier. The tier determines how many somatic components define the spell:
Novice Spells: 1 somatic component
Apprentice Spells: 2 somatic components
Adept Spells: 3 somatic components
Expert Spells: 4 somatic components
Master Spells: 5 somatic components
More complex spells require more somatic components to define them. A Novice spell is simple; a Master spell is intricate.
